Creating images with R

with a little bit of magick

Kevin Lee

My meme


I created this meme to summarize my feelings on having to learn another language. 

#REQUIRED PACKAGES:
library(magick)
library(tidyverse)

#Creates top-half of meme
top_half <- image_read(path = "https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod/images/womanyellingcat-1573233850.jpg?crop=0.75xw:1xh;center,top&resize=1200:*") %>%
  image_scale(800)

#Creates 1st text box for meme
first_text_box <- image_blank(width = 400, height = 50, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate("Learning another lanuage\nthat isn't python", color ="#000000", size = 25, font = "Impact", gravity = "center")

#Creates 2nd text box for meme
second_text_box <- image_blank(width = 400, height = 50, color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "STATS220", color ="#000000", size = 30, font = "Impact", gravity = "center")

#Combines both boxes to create bottom half of meme
bottom_half <- image_append(c(first_text_box, second_text_box))  

#Appends both top and bottom halves to create meme
meme <- c(top_half, bottom_half) %>%
  image_append(stack= TRUE) %>%
    image_scale(500)

#Writes meme
image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")


My animated GIF


I like dogs and puns. 

#REQUIRED PACKAGES:
library(magick)
library(tidyverse)
#TODO:
  # use comments

#Read image
dog_image <- image_read(path = "https://imgflip.com/s/meme/Bad-Pun-Dog.jpg")

#Create frames
frame1 <- image_crop(dog_image, "1000x350+100") %>%
    image_scale(500)

frame2 <- image_crop(dog_image, "1000x300+100+370") %>%
  image_scale(500)

frame3 <- image_crop(dog_image, "1000x600+100+670") %>%
  image_scale(500)

frame4 <- image_read(path = "https://i.kym-cdn.com/photos/images/newsfeed/001/504/503/cef.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

#Add text to each frame
frame1 <- image_annotate(frame1, "Why did the functions stop calling each other?",font="impact", size=25, gravity = "south", color = "white",boxcolor = "black")
frame2 <- image_annotate(frame2, "Because they had constant arguments.",font="impact", size=30, gravity = "south", color = "white",boxcolor = "black")

#Create frame vector
frames <- c(frame1,frame2,frame3,frame4)

#Create and save gif
image_write(image_animate(frames, fps = 1), "my_animation.gif")
